			<div class="content" id="post-content-4165890">
									

<p>Seeing this in action makes this apparent how unhelpful this is. This isn't going to help visibility at all. Couple reasons:</p>
<ul>
<li>The easiest way to read through recently created SCPs and remember where you left off was by judging off location between non-SCP writing. I could look at the old list and say &quot;I have read all SCPs between these two tales, with non SCP names. The only way to do this as it stands is through -EX and -Js, which are not particularly common.</li>
<li>To get to GoI formats and other pages, you have to scroll past the entirety of the other two lists, which are fairly long. On mobile, you need to scroll past SCPs to get to tales, tales to get to GoIs and GoIs to get to other stuff. This makes content unnecessarily difficult to even see.</li>
<li><em>Untagged pages</em> have been relegated to the bottom right corner, mixed in with any other page. This separates and buries new SCP articles. Are there plans to dramatically increase the rate at which SCPs are tagged, in order to facilitate this? This seems like it will act as an unnecessary burden on Tech, or at the very least tempt users into tagging their own works, which is not something Tech generally wants.</li>
<li>If I want to see what new articles have been posted since I last checked, I know need to visit four separate lists in turn, rather than a single one. A minor inconvenience, but still present.</li>
<li>There's also some general clunkiness that comes from have four page separated listpage modules on the same page - you have to go to the next page on every list if you want to see more articles.</li>
</ul>

